 each constraint corresponds to a property that can be used to partition
 the domain of entities into two classes (i.e.
 the class of entities that all have the property, and the class of entities
 that all do not).
 The addition of a new constraint re-partitions all classes specified by
 existing constraints, such that the total number of candidate equivalence
